The truth ran like a spear through heart. If not for the armour which healed and the earing which caught Adhirath's eyes. The boy whould've drowned. I would've dorwned. Gone, never to exist. Is that what she wanted? For me to just become a torn page of her past!? Or did she knew I would survive due to my gifts? And she bet all of it on that! I didn't know which truth was the worse. I didn't wanted to know.  I didn't want to go back to those sleep. Awaking, lonely and tired moments were preferred than those haunting nightmares. Even if they became a hazy blur only few moments later. }
